Etymology.
The species name acknowledges late Reinhard Förster (
1935–1987
) and Pál Müller (
1935–2015
), who were among the first to collect and figure the material belonging to this species.

Type material.
Holotype : HNHM M.86.64A , right propodus
.
Paratypes : HNHM M.86.64B , right propodus
;
HNHM M.86.64C , right propodus
;
HNHM M.86.64D , left propodus
;
HNHM M.86.64E , right propodus
;
HNHM M.86.64F , left propodus
;
HNHM M.86.64G , left propodus
. All elements are of major pereiopod 1 (cheliped) coming from the Örs vezér tere ( MOE ) locality in Budapest , Hungary .

